From: Antigravity <antigravity@google.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 14:05:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] io_uring: document low-latency mode and registered buffer recommendation

In deterministic workloads, the memory management overhead of standard
I/O (pinning and DMA mapping) can be as expensive as the computation itself.
This patch adds a rate-limited warning when a ring configured with
IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY is used with non-fixed buffer operations.

This encourages userspace to adopt the registered-buffer fast path.

Signed-off-by: Antigravity <antigravity@google.com>
---
 io_uring/io_uring.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/io_uring/io_uring.c b/io_uring/io_uring.c
index ...
--- a/io_uring/io_uring.c
+++ b/io_uring/io_uring.c
@@ -1815,6 +1815,14 @@ static int io_issue_sqe(struct io_kiocb *req, unsigned int issue_flags)
 	if (unlikely(!io_assign_file(req, def, issue_flags)))
 		return -EBADF;
 
+	if (unlikely((req->ctx->flags & IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY) &&
+		     !(req->flags & REQ_F_BUF_NODE) &&
+		     (req->opcode == IORING_OP_READ || req->opcode == IORING_OP_WRITE ||
+		      req->opcode == IORING_OP_READV || req->opcode == IORING_OP_WRITEV))) {
+		pr_warn_ratelimited("io_uring: LOW_LATENCY ring used without registered buffers (opcode %d)\n",
+				    req->opcode);
+	}
+
 	ret = __io_issue_sqe(req, issue_flags, def);
 
 	if (ret == IOU_COMPLETE) {
